.TH GEOM_RED 1 2025-Jun "" "Create red channel MS imaging layer Generates a ggplot2 layer for mass spectrometry imaging (MSI) data visualization in red color channel corresponding to specified m/z value."
.SH NAME
geom_red \- geom_red(mz,
    <i>tolerance</i> = 'getOption'('mzdiff', 'default' = 'da:0.3'))
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fIgeom_red(mz,
    <i>tolerance</i> = 'getOption'('mzdiff', 'default' = 'da:0.3'))\fR
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fBmz\fB \fR\- . numeric. The target mass-to-charge ratio (m/z) value for ion detection.
.PP
.PP
\fBtolerance\fB \fR\- 'getOption'('mzdiff', 'default' = 'da:0.3'). character or numeric. Mass accuracy tolerance in Dalton (Da) format. Default uses option "mzdiff" if set, otherwise "da:0.3". Format should follow "da:[value]" for Dalton-based tolerance or "ppm:[value]" for parts-per-million.
.PP
.SH VALUE
.PP
A ggplot2 layer object that can be added to existing MSI plots for multi-channel visualization. Displays ion distribution in red color scale.
.PP
.SH FILES
.PP
SMRUCC/R#.declare_function.geom_red at MSImaging.R:line 18
.PP
